OL,3,CHome Office apology and 'substantial'
OL,4,Cdamages over NI building firm false
OL,5,Cclaims
OL,7,F"The Home Office accepts that FP
OL,8,FMcCann's contractors were lawfully
OL,9,Fentitled to work the site in north
OL,10,FWales. FP McCann has therefore not
OL,11,Fbeen fined by the Home Office."
OL,13,FMr Hopkins added: "The Home Office
OL,14,Fapologises to FP McCann and its
OL,15,Fdirectors for publishing ther false
OL,16,Fand defamatory allegations, and has
OL,17,Fagreed to pay substantial damages, and
OL,18,Freasonable legal costs, as a result of
OL,19,Fthe publication of the erroneous press
OL,20,Frelease."
